      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-hemolysis-bench-5pts",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench hemolysis validation — 5 operating points",
      "description": "In-vitro hemolysis index measured at 5 flow-rate/speed combinations using the FDA generic pump geometry. Predicted RH values compared against measured NIH values; all 5 points satisfy RH < 1. Mean absolute error 4.2%. Turbulence model: SST k-omega with curvature correction. Mesh: 8.4M hexahedral cells.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/uq/vr-hemolysis-bench-uq",
        "type": "UncertaintyQuantification",
        "method": "Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition uncertainty (±5% flow rate) and material property scatter (viscosity ±3%). 95th-percentile prediction interval reported for each operating point.",
        "coverageProbability": 0.95
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-pressure-rise-validation",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Pump pressure-rise validation across speed sweep",
      "description": "Predicted hydraulic head compared against manufacturer-supplied bench data for rotational speeds 2000–4000 RPM in 500 RPM increments. R² = 0.993 across 9 test points. Validates that the CFD solver correctly captures the momentum transfer in the impeller passage, providing confidence in the velocity-field fidelity that underpins the hemolysis scalar transport equation. No uncertainty quantification envelope was computed for this secondary validation result because the hydraulic performance data were treated as deterministic reference values by the assessment team."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-wall-shear-piv",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress — PIV comparison in volute",
      "description": "Particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements in the volute exit region compared with CFD predictions at the nominal operating point (3 L/min, 3500 RPM). Velocity magnitude within 7% of PIV ensemble average. Confirms near-wall flow structure critical for red-blood-cell exposure time estimation.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": {
